WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.753
JAX:
Previously on Reasonable Doubt...

00:02.753 --> 00:03.879
- It's been a long time.

00:03.879 --> 00:05.088
- Sixteen years.

00:05.088 --> 00:06.632
I can't be here anymore.

00:06.632 --> 00:08.759
And the only way to do that
is to show remorse.

00:08.759 --> 00:12.012
JAX:
I cannot believe my dad stood me up again.

00:12.012 --> 00:14.056
I really wish
you would have forgiven Daddy

00:14.056 --> 00:15.641
the same way you forgave Paul.

00:15.641 --> 00:18.060
- Well, I can't see you
being a public defender.

00:18.060 --> 00:20.187
- Once a PD, always a PD.

00:20.187 --> 00:21.605
- I know you and Lewis have your issues,

00:21.605 --> 00:23.857
but you should really
think about making it work.

00:23.857 --> 00:25.901
JAX: She up here staying
with her cheating-ass husband

00:25.901 --> 00:27.778
and wanna give me relationship advice.

00:27.778 --> 00:28.820
- You know what would be dope?

00:28.820 --> 00:30.614
If we could be friends.

00:30.614 --> 00:33.951
I could stay in jail
and dream of this life that I could have

00:33.951 --> 00:35.202
or I could actually live it.

00:35.202 --> 00:37.454
Your husband's okay
with friends coming over?

00:37.454 --> 00:39.248
JAX:
Actually, we're separated.

00:39.248 --> 00:41.333
- He is an idiot to let you go.

00:42.042 --> 00:44.962
♪

00:44.962 --> 00:50.968
♪

00:50.968 --> 00:54.179
♪

00:59.226 --> 01:00.352
- Ladies and gentlemen,

01:01.395 --> 01:03.063
the people just told you

01:03.063 --> 01:06.692
that their case is
clear, solid, definitive,

01:07.484 --> 01:10.237
that Mr. Uribe is the only person

01:10.237 --> 01:12.072
who could have committed this crime.

01:12.531 --> 01:16.660
But I will lay out to you
all the ways their theory is flawed.

01:16.660 --> 01:18.954
Was there a solid chain of custody

01:18.954 --> 01:20.831
when it came to the physical evidence?

01:20.831 --> 01:21.832
No.

01:22.291 --> 01:25.752
Was Mr. Uribe the only Latino man
in the park

01:25.752 --> 01:27.171
at the time of the assault?

01:28.005 --> 01:29.006
No.

01:29.006 --> 01:31.216
Were there other people
in the victim's life

01:31.216 --> 01:32.718
who were motivated to harm him

01:32.718 --> 01:35.554
that could not be accounted for
the night of the crime?

01:36.305 --> 01:37.306
Yes.

01:37.681 --> 01:39.683
That to me sounds like a case

01:39.683 --> 01:41.768
with a whole lot of reasonable doubt.

01:43.145 --> 01:44.146
But you know what?

01:44.813 --> 01:46.106
I don't have to prove that to you.

01:46.690 --> 01:48.525
That's the people's burden,

01:48.525 --> 01:49.735
not yours.

01:49.735 --> 01:52.654
All I'm asking you to do is to listen.

01:53.488 --> 01:55.991
Listen to the facts, and lack thereof,

01:55.991 --> 02:00.078
in order to prevent an innocent man
from going into the prison system

02:00.078 --> 02:02.206
and becoming something he is not.

02:02.915 --> 02:03.916
Thank you.

02:07.085 --> 02:08.337
JUDGE:
Members of the jury,

02:08.337 --> 02:11.465
you may now retire to the jury room
to begin deliberation.

02:13.425 --> 02:14.426
- Hector?

02:23.602 --> 02:25.812
Um-- Okay. I know I said I wanted
to practice my Spanish,

02:25.812 --> 02:28.857
but I don't know how to ask
why you would wanna take a plea

02:28.857 --> 02:31.485
to go to jail for
a crime you didn't commit?

02:31.485 --> 02:33.779
- My entire life, things don't go my way.

02:34.488 --> 02:35.572
So why would they now?

02:35.572 --> 02:37.407
- Because you got me, Hector.

02:37.407 --> 02:39.201
When I go to trial, I win.

02:39.201 --> 02:41.411
- And I really appreciate
all your hard work,

02:41.411 --> 02:43.747
but... I'm done.

02:45.082 --> 02:46.083
- Hector.

