04:18.592 --> 04:21.053
- Court has set bail at $500,000.

04:21.053 --> 04:22.513
- Any chance you can get that lowered?

04:22.513 --> 04:24.932
- You're being charged
with second-degree murder, Mr. Cooke.

04:24.932 --> 04:26.517
By law that's the number.

04:26.517 --> 04:28.477
- Alright, fine. What about Rafael?

04:28.477 --> 04:31.146
- Your codefendant, Mr. Coleman,
is also being charged with murder.

04:31.146 --> 04:33.774
- Fuck, I can't believe
this shit is happening.

04:33.774 --> 04:35.567
JAX:
Take a breath, Mr. Cooke.

04:35.567 --> 04:37.778
Why don't you tell me about yourself?
Where you from?

04:37.778 --> 04:39.613
- Where I'm from--

04:41.490 --> 04:42.741
[sighs]

04:42.741 --> 04:44.952
I grew up on West 67th off Buckler.

04:44.952 --> 04:46.703
- That's Rollin' 60s territory.

04:47.579 --> 04:48.789
- They wouldn't let me in.

04:51.124 --> 04:52.793
- Are you employed, Mr. Cooke?

04:52.793 --> 04:54.294
- I run an auto shop off Leimert.

04:55.587 --> 04:57.589
Took over when my daddy passed away.

04:57.589 --> 04:58.632
JAX:
Education?

04:59.591 --> 05:03.637
- Graduated St. Bernard's.
Westchester, South LA.

05:03.637 --> 05:06.682
- I'm from Crenshaw and Coliseum,
went to Fairfax,

05:06.682 --> 05:08.809
so I know where St. Bernard's is.

05:09.560 --> 05:11.979
Uh, the night of the murder,
can you tell me what happened?

05:14.356 --> 05:15.941
- Yeah, so me and my homeboy, we was, uh--

05:15.941 --> 05:18.360
- That's Mr. Coleman?
- Yeah. Rafael.

05:18.360 --> 05:20.988
We went out to this spot
called Bottoms Up in Hawthorne

05:20.988 --> 05:23.031
and, you know, we ordered some drinks,

05:23.031 --> 05:24.533
and Rafael was hollering at a few

05:26.493 --> 05:29.204
women and whatnot and then, uh,

05:29.204 --> 05:31.415
this dude started beefing with Rafael

05:31.415 --> 05:33.041
and he wouldn't stop running his mouth.

05:33.750 --> 05:36.587
So then he tried to accuse Rafael
of getting with his girl and--

05:36.587 --> 05:38.547
- Okay. Is that the victim, Kevin Chapman?

05:39.965 --> 05:40.966
- Yeah.

05:40.966 --> 05:42.718
- Okay, what happened next?

05:42.718 --> 05:44.386
- Then all hell broke loose.

05:44.386 --> 05:46.096
I was getting hit from all sides

05:46.096 --> 05:48.265
and just trying to keep
motherfuckers off me and shit.

05:48.265 --> 05:50.350
- Well, this complaint says
that you fled the scene.

05:50.350 --> 05:52.352
You told the police
that you weren't involved in a fight.

05:53.020 --> 05:54.479
Why did you lie?

05:54.479 --> 05:55.647
DAMON:
I ain't flee.

05:55.647 --> 05:57.107
Or whatever it is they trying to say.

05:58.859 --> 06:01.570
I ain't kill nobody. I-I-I left.

06:01.570 --> 06:03.864
I got a business. I got responsibilities.

06:08.493 --> 06:10.412
So what happens next, Fairfax?

06:10.954 --> 06:13.207
- Well... well, that depends.

06:13.707 --> 06:17.461
I can go to the DA, see about a plea,
or we can fight it in trial.

06:17.461 --> 06:18.504
- Wait, wait. You said a plea.

06:19.588 --> 06:21.673
You mean to say I'm guilty?
- Yes.

06:22.257 --> 06:23.509
- But I'm innocent.

06:23.509 --> 06:25.802
- So you wanna go to trial?
- I mean--

06:27.304 --> 06:28.305
What do you think?

06:31.016 --> 06:33.852
- Let me dig into your case a bit,
see what we're up against.

06:33.852 --> 06:36.563
I'll go to the DA
and come back to you with some options.

06:36.563 --> 06:39.608
- Alright. I mean,
I can, I can rock with that.

06:39.608 --> 06:41.068
- I'll try to make it quick
so you can get back

06:41.068 --> 06:43.028
to your ambitions
of a Rollin 60s ridah.

06:46.782 --> 06:48.784
- You got jokes?
- Sorry. I--

06:48.784 --> 06:50.118
- That was a good one.

06:50.619 --> 06:51.620
- Thanks. [clears throat]

06:52.329 --> 06:53.372
Anyway,

06:54.414 --> 06:57.125
I have 35 other cases
that need my attention, Mr. Cooke.

06:57.125 --> 06:58.252
So unless you have any other--

06:58.252 --> 07:00.379
- Good luck with your other cases.

07:01.755 --> 07:07.010
♪

07:07.010 --> 07:08.679
NEWSCASTER: [on TV]
An unusual mishap in a construction zone

07:08.679 --> 07:11.431
near the 10-110 interchange
occurred this afternoon,

07:11.431 --> 07:12.808
leaving the 10 freeway backed up
to Crenshaw.

07:12.808 --> 07:13.809
[cell phone ringing]

07:13.809 --> 07:16.270
[newscaster continues indistinctly]

07:16.270 --> 07:17.813
[ringing continues]

07:19.565 --> 07:21.191
- Hello?
- Hey, girl. What you doing?

07:21.191 --> 07:22.860
- Sitting here watching the news.

07:22.860 --> 07:24.486
I feel like I'm turning into my mother.

07:24.945 --> 07:25.946
What you up to?

07:25.946 --> 07:27.197
AUTUMN: [over phone]
Reading these case studies.

07:27.614 --> 07:29.157
Are you bringing anyone
to Sally's wedding?

07:29.157 --> 07:30.826
- Nope. You?

07:30.826 --> 07:33.495
- I was gonna bring Kendall,
but it's too soon.

07:33.495 --> 07:34.496
- Hmm.

07:35.163 --> 07:38.333
Okay, Autumn, when are you
gonna tell the other girls

07:38.333 --> 07:39.918
that Kendall is not just your roommate?

07:39.918 --> 07:41.962
- I don't know. I feel like
you're more understanding.

07:41.962 --> 07:43.547
- They'll understand.

07:43.547 --> 07:44.548
- Maybe.

07:45.340 --> 07:46.341
What about you?

07:46.341 --> 07:49.011
- Uh, no. I am too busy for love.

07:49.011 --> 07:50.179
- It doesn't work that way.

07:50.179 --> 07:52.681
- Okay, well, then I'm too busy
to have my heart broken.

07:52.681 --> 07:56.810
- Yeah, yeah, but remember,
Jax, sharing is caring.

07:56.810 --> 07:57.811
- Hmm.

07:58.187 --> 07:59.688
How about you practice what you preach?

08:01.356 --> 08:03.108
Huh?
Bye, Autumn.

08:03.984 --> 08:04.985
AUTUMN:
Bye, girl.

08:08.071 --> 08:11.116
- I've gone over Damon Cooke's case
and there are quite a few holes.

08:11.116 --> 08:12.743
- Okay, what are they?

08:13.285 --> 08:15.329
- Well, first of all,
the surveillance video

08:15.329 --> 08:17.664
doesn't make it clear
that Mr. Cooke committed a crime.

08:17.664 --> 08:19.833
- What about the witness?
- Come on, Miguel.

08:19.833 --> 08:22.252
We all know eyewitness testimony
is never enough,

08:22.252 --> 08:25.088
especially late at night
in that dark-ass bar

08:25.088 --> 08:26.965
from a person working the night shift.

08:26.965 --> 08:29.051
- Fine. What else?

08:29.051 --> 08:32.638
- Mr. Cooke is a business owner
without a criminal past.

08:32.638 --> 08:35.891
He's also a fairly
mild-mannered individual

08:35.891 --> 08:37.559
who barely drinks.

08:37.559 --> 08:41.313
So, what, we're supposed to believe
that he suddenly got so drunk

08:41.313 --> 08:43.398
that he decided to pierce flesh?

08:43.398 --> 08:45.442
I mean, come on, that's a reach.

08:45.442 --> 08:47.361
- So then you wanna go to trial?

08:47.361 --> 08:48.403
JAX:
I do.

08:48.403 --> 08:50.531
But, you know, I at least wanna hear
what you're offering.

08:52.491 --> 08:55.786
- Voluntary manslaughter
midterm of six years in state prison.

08:55.786 --> 08:57.871
- Same charge. One year in County.

08:58.580 --> 09:00.249
- Nice try. Strike one,

09:00.249 --> 09:02.709
Cooke lied to the police.

09:02.709 --> 09:06.004
Strike two, we have witnesses
who say he was the aggressor.

09:06.004 --> 09:08.090
And strike three,
his prints are on the knife.

09:10.759 --> 09:13.387
Oh. You didn't get the report yet?

09:13.387 --> 09:16.014
♪

09:16.014 --> 09:17.432
Still seem like a reach?

09:17.432 --> 09:22.062
♪

09:22.062 --> 09:24.231
- Did you bring a knife
to the bar that night?

09:24.231 --> 09:26.900
- I bring my knife everywhere,
but, shit, it ain't a gun.

09:26.900 --> 09:28.443
- So then you stabbed that man.

09:28.443 --> 09:30.195
- What? No, look.

09:30.195 --> 09:32.990
Alright. It was my knife, yes.

09:32.990 --> 09:36.368
But it fell out of my pocket
during the craziness of the fight.

09:36.368 --> 09:37.953
And somebody must have grabbed it

09:37.953 --> 09:40.122
'cause all of a sudden
it was stuck in this dude's neck.

09:40.122 --> 09:41.582
And I was just like, "What the fuck?"

09:41.582 --> 09:45.210
So then I was gonna pull it out,
and Rafael told me not to.

09:45.210 --> 09:47.296
So then we just, just fucking
broke up out of there.

09:48.964 --> 09:50.883
I'm telling the truth here, I swear.

09:51.592 --> 09:52.885
- You sure you wanna swear on that?

09:54.595 --> 09:56.680
- Isn't it your job to-to-to believe me?

09:56.680 --> 10:00.058
- No. My job is to tell you
what your options are.

10:00.559 --> 10:03.604
And given this new information
that you failed to share with me,

10:04.229 --> 10:07.316
I'm telling you as your attorney
that a trial does not look good for you.

10:07.316 --> 10:09.526
- I didn't do this.
JAX: Look, I spoke to the DA,

10:09.526 --> 10:11.111
and he's offering voluntary manslaughter.

10:11.111 --> 10:12.529
Six years.

10:12.529 --> 10:14.698
With good behavior,
you can be out on parole in two.

10:14.698 --> 10:17.409
If you go to trial,
you'll be fighting a murder charge,

10:17.409 --> 10:18.410
which is 15 to life.

10:22.206 --> 10:23.207
- Fuck!

10:24.917 --> 10:27.336
Alright, what would,
what would you do if you were me?

10:27.336 --> 10:28.712
- I'm not you.

10:28.712 --> 10:29.963
- Oh, I see. Okay.

10:29.963 --> 10:31.965
So you-you don't think
this could happen to you?

10:31.965 --> 10:33.091
- I didn't say that.

10:33.091 --> 10:35.093
- No, no, no.
Just keep it real with me, Fairfax.

10:35.093 --> 10:36.094
Shit, I ain't gonna tell.

10:39.348 --> 10:42.643
- Although the fingerprint evidence
is inconclusive,

10:42.643 --> 10:44.228
it was your knife.

10:44.228 --> 10:45.687
You lied to the cops.

10:47.439 --> 10:50.067
Just take the deal, okay?
You'll be better off.

10:50.067 --> 10:51.151
- Damn.

10:51.151 --> 10:53.529
♪

10:53.529 --> 10:55.155
I thought you was gonna fight for me.

10:56.323 --> 10:58.784
But you just gonna give up on me
like everybody else in my life.

10:58.784 --> 11:01.036
- Mr. Cooke--
- Nah, don't Mr. Cooke me.

11:01.036 --> 11:03.747
♪

11:03.747 --> 11:05.415
You gonna tell me my shit is fucked up,

11:05.415 --> 11:07.376
just tell me my inmate ID number

11:07.376 --> 11:09.878
since that's all
I am to you anyway, alright?

11:09.878 --> 11:12.130
Yeah, I'll take the fucking deal.

11:12.130 --> 11:16.677
♪

11:16.677 --> 11:18.720
♪

11:18.720 --> 11:19.805
[sighs]

11:24.226 --> 11:26.562
MAMA LU:
It's so wonderful Sally found a man

11:26.562 --> 11:27.771
to spend her life with.

11:27.771 --> 11:30.357
Even though she was
a fast little old thing

11:30.357 --> 11:31.525
when y'all were in high school.

11:31.525 --> 11:33.026
- Ooh. Ma!

11:33.026 --> 11:34.987
- I'm just speaking the truth.
[chuckles]

11:34.987 --> 11:37.531
You know, you're just as pretty as Sally.

11:37.531 --> 11:39.700
No reason you should be
sitting home alone.

11:40.242 --> 11:42.619
- I'm not sitting home alone, Mom.

11:43.036 --> 11:45.455
I mean, I'm not even 30, so I have time.

11:45.455 --> 11:48.041
- Yeah, that's what my friend Debbie
said years ago.

11:48.041 --> 11:51.253
Now she can't even remember her name,
let alone find a man.

11:51.253 --> 11:54.548
- Oh, so I should find a boyfriend
before I get Alzheimer's?

11:54.548 --> 11:56.967
- Oh. Oh, it's something to think about.

11:56.967 --> 11:58.552
- [chuckles] Mom.
- Ooh-ooh.

11:59.928 --> 12:01.847
Why don't you wear this one?

12:01.847 --> 12:05.100
- I know, I was thinking about it,
but that's revealing, don't you think?

12:05.100 --> 12:08.645
- Well, if you don't want it,
I might take it.

12:09.605 --> 12:11.523
I could use a fish of my own.

12:11.523 --> 12:12.691
- No.

12:12.691 --> 12:15.861
- I haven't found anybody
to keep me company since Paul.

12:17.070 --> 12:19.114
Actually, he called the other day.

12:19.114 --> 12:20.657
- Paul did?
- Yeah.

12:20.657 --> 12:22.451
- And?
- And nothing.

12:22.451 --> 12:24.828
I don't think it's a good idea
that we talk

12:24.828 --> 12:27.164
after what happened between us.

12:28.957 --> 12:30.167
No, you're right.

12:30.167 --> 12:32.044
This is too revealing.

12:32.044 --> 12:33.253
Well, why don't you buy something new?

12:33.253 --> 12:35.506
Buy something that'll make
Jonathan jealous.

12:35.506 --> 12:38.717
- Ugh! I don't care
about making Jonathan jealous.

12:38.717 --> 12:41.428
Besides, I can't even afford a new dress.

12:41.428 --> 12:44.806
God, this wedding is costing me a fortune.

12:44.806 --> 12:47.476
- Well, you could always move home
to save some money.

12:47.476 --> 12:48.977
- I know, Mom. I know.

12:49.770 --> 12:52.814
Oh, hell. It's getting late.
I have court in the morning.

12:53.899 --> 12:56.151
Ugh. [sighs]
Look, I'll just--

12:57.027 --> 12:59.821
I'll go to Fox Hills
and find something tomorrow.

13:00.447 --> 13:02.199
- I thought you said
you didn't have enough money

13:02.199 --> 13:03.242
to buy a new dress.

13:03.242 --> 13:05.202
- I'll put it on layaway,
skip lunch this week.

13:05.202 --> 13:06.328
Mwah!

13:06.912 --> 13:09.915
- Oh, Jesus. Help my child.

13:10.499 --> 13:16.255
♪

13:30.102 --> 13:34.648
- So I was rereading your file last night
and I had a realization.

13:35.732 --> 13:38.694
Your codefendant Rafael Coleman
has a criminal past.

13:39.236 --> 13:41.363
And because you guys
look like you can be brothers,

13:41.363 --> 13:43.073
there's an argument to be made

13:43.073 --> 13:46.618
that the DA's eyewitness
misidentified you for Rafael.

13:46.618 --> 13:48.161
- You saying Rafael did this?

13:48.161 --> 13:49.454
- Possibly.

13:49.454 --> 13:52.082
If your prints are conclusive
on the knife, maybe his are.

13:52.833 --> 13:53.959
