Sorry, I didn't realize how big it was.

27:58.512 --> 27:59.888
You ladies wanna feel it?

27:59.888 --> 28:01.765
- Never say those words to us again.

28:02.683 --> 28:05.143
Also, who did you pay to get this award?

28:05.143 --> 28:08.605
They usually give it to corporate types
like Emily or PD's like me.

28:08.605 --> 28:11.400
- They finally realized that
the real stars are at the DA's office.

28:11.400 --> 28:13.193
- Oh, a real epiphany.

28:13.777 --> 28:16.321
- You guys can learn a lot
doing prosecutorial work.

28:16.321 --> 28:19.199
- Oh, you mean like using scared young men
like Rafael Coleman

28:19.199 --> 28:21.451
to build cases against innocent Black men?

28:21.451 --> 28:24.371
- Damon Cooke is not innocent. Sorry.

28:24.371 --> 28:26.248
EMILY:
Or you could move to a corporate firm.

28:26.248 --> 28:27.249
I just did.

28:27.249 --> 28:29.168
And frankly,
I sleep a lot easier at night.

28:29.168 --> 28:30.460
- What do you mean?

28:30.460 --> 28:32.421
EMILY:
The stakes are significantly lower.

28:32.421 --> 28:34.631
Think about it. If I win, great.

28:34.631 --> 28:37.551
And if I don't,
those rich, entitled assholes

28:37.551 --> 28:38.969
probably deserved it.

28:38.969 --> 28:41.805
- I don't wanna represent
rich, entitled assholes.

28:41.805 --> 28:44.183
I represent people
who have nowhere else to turn.

28:44.183 --> 28:46.518
If the system wants to take away
someone's liberty,

28:46.518 --> 28:48.145
their-their freedom,

28:48.145 --> 28:49.605
they're gonna need a high burden of proof.

28:49.605 --> 28:52.065
And they're gonna
have to go through me, period.

28:54.526 --> 28:56.570
- Inspiring.
- Eat a dick.

28:56.570 --> 28:58.697
- And how's it feel when you lose, Jax?

28:58.697 --> 29:01.074
- Either way, you've paid your dues, Jax.

29:01.074 --> 29:03.160
It's time to move on.
EMILY: Mm-hmm.

29:03.160 --> 29:06.038
Oh, and it's time for me to go home.

29:06.038 --> 29:07.414
Get that good sleep.

29:07.414 --> 29:08.582
Later, peeps.

29:08.582 --> 29:09.583
JAX:
See ya.

29:10.751 --> 29:14.671
- You know, I don't intend
to stay at the DA's office forever.

29:15.088 --> 29:17.174
- Hmm.
MIKE: I got much bigger plans.

29:17.174 --> 29:19.927
You're looking at
the first Latino governor of California.

29:20.719 --> 29:22.179
You ever thought about
getting into politics?

29:22.179 --> 29:24.306
- Uh-- [scoffs]
- You and me could make a play for it.

29:25.057 --> 29:26.391
You know what they say.

29:26.391 --> 29:27.684
Behind every great man--

29:27.684 --> 29:29.228
- Is a woman rolling her eyes?

29:29.228 --> 29:30.437
- No, but, come on, for real. Seriously.

29:31.104 --> 29:32.397
You never thought about it?

29:32.397 --> 29:37.236
You, me, bringing two of LA's
biggest constituencies together,

29:37.236 --> 29:39.655
showing off our cute Afro-Latino babies.

29:42.741 --> 29:46.328
- Oh, my God. Please.

29:46.328 --> 29:47.579
Are you serious?

29:47.579 --> 29:49.414
[Jax laughing]

29:49.414 --> 29:50.499
Hmm.

29:50.999 --> 29:52.042
You know what?

29:52.042 --> 29:55.170
I think you and your little award
need some alone time.

29:55.170 --> 29:57.673
I'll see you in court... Mike.

29:57.673 --> 30:00.843
♪

30:00.843 --> 30:02.261
- [sighs] Okay.

30:07.182 --> 30:08.684
[sighs]

30:14.106 --> 30:16.400
[cell phone buzzing]

30:18.110 --> 30:19.444
- This is Jax.

30:19.444 --> 30:20.654
DAMON: [over phone]
Hey, did I wake you?

30:22.447 --> 30:23.448
- Damon?

30:24.825 --> 30:29.037
Uh, they let you
make a phone call this time of night?

30:29.037 --> 30:31.290
- My brother put some money
on my commissary.

30:31.290 --> 30:32.791
I traded for a burner.

30:34.042 --> 30:35.502
Why you up so late?

30:35.502 --> 30:37.880
- Uh, I was actually
just about to go to sleep.

30:39.089 --> 30:41.550
Why are you awake?
DAMON: Uh--

30:41.550 --> 30:43.385
Rafael lying on me and shit.

30:44.595 --> 30:46.263
I thought that nigga was a friend.

30:46.722 --> 30:47.723
- I'm sorry.

30:48.182 --> 30:49.433
- You okay?

30:49.433 --> 30:53.103
JAX: [over phone]
Me? Uh... yeah, I mean--

30:53.103 --> 30:54.104
Well--

30:55.314 --> 30:57.983
Actually, my best friend
is getting married tomorrow.

30:59.067 --> 31:01.653
And, I mean, I'm happy for her.
I guess I just--

31:03.989 --> 31:06.450
I don't know, I feel like
everyone around me is

31:06.450 --> 31:10.954
coupling up and finding someone,
and I'm just hella single.

31:12.122 --> 31:15.000
I'm so sorry. I should not be
sharing any of this with you.

31:16.168 --> 31:18.003
DAMON:
No, no, no, it's nice. It's nice.

31:19.588 --> 31:20.589
I like it.

31:21.548 --> 31:25.010
I mean, you know, I'm sure you got dudes
trying to get with you all the time.

31:25.010 --> 31:27.304
- [scoffs] Not the right ones.

31:27.304 --> 31:29.765
- Would you know if you found him?
JAX: I hope so.

31:29.765 --> 31:32.726
Isn't that what they say,
when you know, you know?

31:33.310 --> 31:35.479
- I don't know.
[Jax chuckles]

31:36.605 --> 31:38.482
JAX:
I thought I was in love once,

31:38.482 --> 31:40.150
but, nah, maybe it's me.

31:40.150 --> 31:41.777
My friends say I'm guarded.

31:41.777 --> 31:45.280
I don't know how to... open up.

31:45.280 --> 31:47.324
- And yet you opened up with me.

31:49.243 --> 31:50.953
- Um-- [clears throat]

31:50.953 --> 31:52.663
- You seem uncomfortable, Jax.

31:53.914 --> 31:54.915
- I am.

31:55.457 --> 31:56.625
DAMON:
Sometimes being uncomfortable

31:56.625 --> 31:57.793
is a good thing.

31:57.793 --> 32:00.796
It gets you out of your head
when you're thinking too much.

32:01.213 --> 32:03.298
- I think a lot.

32:04.967 --> 32:06.927
- What you thinking about now?

32:11.348 --> 32:13.350
- What are you thinking about?

32:13.350 --> 32:14.977
♪

32:14.977 --> 32:16.061
- You.

32:16.061 --> 32:21.358
♪

32:21.358 --> 32:24.444
♪

32:24.444 --> 32:25.612
- Oh, yeah?

32:26.488 --> 32:27.573
- Always.

32:27.573 --> 32:33.495
♪

32:39.418 --> 32:40.419
[moans softly]

32:40.419 --> 32:41.837
♪

32:41.837 --> 32:43.797
- What are you doing to me?

32:43.797 --> 32:45.924
- Same thing you're doing to me.

32:46.925 --> 32:50.846
♪

32:54.183 --> 32:55.350
[Jax moans]

32:55.350 --> 32:56.935
♪

33:05.819 --> 33:06.987
[Jax moans]

33:07.654 --> 33:12.367
♪

33:12.367 --> 33:13.577
Good night, Jax.

33:13.577 --> 33:19.583
♪

33:19.583 --> 33:20.584
[sighs]

33:20.584 --> 33:23.295
♪

33:23.295 --> 33:25.172
♪ I Can't Help Myself
by Loleatta Holloway playing ♪

33:25.172 --> 33:27.674
[cheering]

33:27.674 --> 33:30.427
♪

33:30.427 --> 33:33.096
EMCEE:
And now, everyone, please gather around

33:33.096 --> 33:34.890
for the father-daughter dance.

33:34.890 --> 33:37.309
♪

33:37.309 --> 33:39.102
♪

33:39.102 --> 33:43.190
♪

33:43.190 --> 33:45.901
♪ I never thought ♪

33:45.901 --> 33:48.403
♪ I could fall in love ♪

33:48.403 --> 33:50.864
♪ With a guy like you ♪

33:50.864 --> 33:53.700
♪

33:53.700 --> 33:54.701
- What's up?

33:55.953 --> 33:58.247
- Girl, I can't believe
Jamarion didn't show.

33:58.747 --> 34:00.082
I mean, he said he was gonna be late,

34:00.082 --> 34:02.251
but now it's looking like
he ain't coming at all.

34:02.251 --> 34:04.920
JAX:
Oh. I'm sorry, girl.

34:06.380 --> 34:08.215
Hmm?
- Yes, thank you.

34:08.215 --> 34:09.633
[Jax chuckles]

34:09.633 --> 34:12.010
[applause]

34:12.010 --> 34:15.764
♪

34:15.764 --> 34:17.140
JAX:
You know what?

34:17.140 --> 34:19.059
Your cousin only gets married once.

34:19.560 --> 34:21.895
I really think that you should
get up out this seat

34:21.895 --> 34:23.438
and get back out there.

34:24.147 --> 34:25.774
Jamarion'll make it up to you

34:25.774 --> 34:29.653
with that fat-ass
"I just made All-Pro" bonus money.

34:33.365 --> 34:35.951
- You're right.
- I know.

34:35.951 --> 34:37.327
- Thanks, girl.

34:37.327 --> 34:42.916
♪

34:42.916 --> 34:43.917
Oh--

34:44.668 --> 34:47.546
Sis, don't listen
to what Autumn and Sally have to say.

34:47.546 --> 34:50.340
If you like this nigga,
then like this nigga.

34:50.340 --> 34:54.052
Hell, maybe you win the case
and we all end up boo'd up.

34:54.052 --> 34:55.387
[chuckles]

34:56.263 --> 34:57.806
It's a possibility.

34:57.806 --> 35:02.978
♪

35:28.629 --> 35:29.630
- Hey.

35:30.464 --> 35:31.632
- Hey.

35:32.216 --> 35:33.258
How'd you sleep?

35:34.635 --> 35:35.636
- Good.

35:36.553 --> 35:37.971
Really good.

35:38.680 --> 35:39.681
- Yeah.

35:40.807 --> 35:41.808
Me too.

35:45.938 --> 35:47.940
- We should discuss our case.

35:47.940 --> 35:50.067
- I don't want to talk about the case.

35:50.067 --> 35:51.527
- Damon, we need to go over

35:51.527 --> 35:54.071
your testimony one more time.
- Jax, please.

35:54.571 --> 35:55.572
Not now.

35:57.783 --> 35:58.951
- Okay.

35:58.951 --> 36:03.997
♪

36:10.087 --> 36:11.213
- I think about

36:12.589 --> 36:14.258
what it would be like to just,

36:15.092 --> 36:16.301
to just sit somewhere,

36:17.886 --> 36:19.555
you know, just the two of us.

36:20.848 --> 36:21.974
Just to talk.

36:22.933 --> 36:24.309
Beyond these walls

36:26.353 --> 36:28.355
and without time limits.

36:28.355 --> 36:31.817
♪

36:31.817 --> 36:33.235
- I think about that too.

36:33.235 --> 36:35.612
♪

36:35.612 --> 36:36.905
- You do?

36:36.905 --> 36:38.365
♪

36:38.365 --> 36:39.366
- I do.

36:42.494 --> 36:44.872
Everything hinges on Damon's testimony.

36:44.872 --> 36:47.249
I can't fuck this up.
- Language.

36:47.249 --> 36:48.876
- A man's life is at stake.

36:48.876 --> 36:51.670
- Focus on Miguel and the case he's built.

36:51.670 --> 36:53.088
I don't care what that damn school says.

36:53.088 --> 36:54.464
You a better lawyer than him.

36:54.464 --> 36:58.385
Jacqueline, you are the smartest person
in any room you're in.

36:58.385 --> 37:01.930
Remember that and your client
will walk out of there a free man.

37:02.806 --> 37:03.849
- Thank you, Ma.

37:05.475 --> 37:07.352
- We can talk more later if you need.

37:07.352 --> 37:09.146
- Oh.
- I gotta head out.

37:09.146 --> 37:12.065
- Uh, well, don't you need
to get dressed first?

37:23.285 --> 37:25.162
- I've learned a lot about myself

37:25.162 --> 37:26.663
in the past few years.

37:27.456 --> 37:28.540
I'm an alcoholic.

37:29.541 --> 37:31.376
And I've done some things

37:31.793 --> 37:33.629
when I was drinking that I'm not proud of.

37:36.590 --> 37:37.591
And I'm sorry.

37:39.343 --> 37:40.719
I'm ten years sober now.

37:42.179 --> 37:43.388
I'm not the same guy.

37:44.932 --> 37:47.643
- I think it was good for us
to have this time apart

37:47.643 --> 37:49.895
so that Paul could get himself together.

37:51.396 --> 37:54.399
I'm proud of how far he's come.

37:55.609 --> 37:57.319
- Oh, so, so this is happening.

37:58.153 --> 37:59.238
You're getting back together.

38:03.075 --> 38:05.577
Unbelievable.
MAMA LU: Jacqueline.

38:07.120 --> 38:09.540
Jacqueline! Jacqueline, wait. Please!

38:11.333 --> 38:13.293
JAX: Are you really gonna
pretend like nothing happened?

38:14.044 --> 38:15.295
MAMA LU:
He made a mistake.

38:15.295 --> 38:18.173
- Yes, but why does he deserve
another chance from me or from you?

38:18.173 --> 38:20.133
- Every day you fight
for people's second chances.

38:20.133 --> 38:21.218
What's the difference?

38:21.218 --> 38:22.803
- The difference
is that you are my mother

38:22.803 --> 38:24.096
and I expect more from you.

38:24.096 --> 38:26.306
But you always choose yourself first.

38:26.849 --> 38:29.268
You failed me then
and you are failing me now.

38:29.268 --> 38:32.437
- You weren't
the only one hurt, Jacqueline.

38:32.437 --> 38:34.022
I was hurt too. I loved him.

38:34.731 --> 38:38.235
One day you will love someone
really, truly love someone

38:38.235 --> 38:41.363
and you will see that
it's not that easy to let 'em go.

38:41.363 --> 38:44.199
- If this is what love looks like,
then I feel sorry for both of us.

38:45.450 --> 38:50.205
♪

38:50.205 --> 38:51.707
♪

38:55.711 --> 38:57.171
CJ:
Oh. Hey. Uh--

38:58.005 --> 38:59.131
You're Damon's lawyer, right?

38:59.131 --> 39:01.175
- Yes.
- I'm his brother CJ.

39:01.175 --> 39:03.969
- CJ! It's nice to meet you.
I've heard a lot about you.

39:03.969 --> 39:06.346
- And you, too.
Thanks for fighting for him.

39:06.930 --> 39:08.432
Means a lot to him and to me.

39:08.432 --> 39:09.433
- Of course.

39:10.809 --> 39:12.019
- He can't go away for this.

39:12.019 --> 39:13.562
I can't be out here by myself.

39:13.562 --> 39:14.563
- You won't be.

39:16.481 --> 39:17.649
Thanks.

39:17.649 --> 39:18.692
JUDGE COOMBS:
Do you promise to tell the truth,

39:18.692 --> 39:20.527
the whole truth,
and nothing but the truth?

39:21.028 --> 39:22.029
- I do.

39:33.957 --> 39:35.501
- Mr. Cooke,

39:35.501 --> 39:37.961
why were you the last person
fighting with Mr. Chapman?

39:37.961 --> 39:39.379
- I didn't know I was.

39:39.922 --> 39:42.216
I just felt myself getting hit.

39:42.216 --> 39:44.343
- You didn't flee the scene,
did you, Mr. Cooke?

39:44.343 --> 39:45.344
- I left.

39:45.969 --> 39:46.970
I, um--

39:48.055 --> 39:50.974
I knew I had been in a fight.
I just didn't want any trouble.

39:50.974 --> 39:51.975
Uh--

39:52.851 --> 39:54.061
I wish I had stuck around.

39:54.061 --> 39:55.646
That was, that was a mistake.

39:57.022 --> 39:59.316
- Did you know Mr. Chapman
before that night?

39:59.316 --> 40:00.901
- Never seen him before in my life.

40:02.027 --> 40:04.279
- Did you stab Kevin Chapman?

40:05.405 --> 40:06.406
- No.

40:11.703 --> 40:12.788
I didn't do it.

40:14.790 --> 40:16.041
- Nothing further.

40:16.917 --> 40:18.877
JUDGE COOMBS:
Mr. Ortiz, your witness.

40:19.670 --> 40:21.255
- You said you jumped into the fight

40:21.255 --> 40:24.383
because your friend
Rafael Coleman needed help, correct?

40:24.967 --> 40:26.009
- Yeah.

40:26.009 --> 40:28.220
- Mr. Chapman
was winning the fight, wasn't he?

40:28.220 --> 40:29.972
- I-I don't know.

40:29.972 --> 40:31.139
MIKE:
Well, at some point,

40:31.139 --> 40:33.392
Mr. Chapman started
getting the better of you.

40:33.392 --> 40:34.977
- Um, I don't think so, no.

40:34.977 --> 40:36.353
MIKE:
Come on, Mr. Cooke.

40:36.353 --> 40:37.938
He was kicking your ass.

40:37.938 --> 40:38.939
- What?

40:39.898 --> 40:41.066
Nah, it wasn't like that.

40:41.066 --> 40:43.944
- Oh, so you were kicking his ass?

40:43.944 --> 40:44.987
- See, I didn't say that.

40:44.987 --> 40:47.072
- Oh, okay, then, Mr. Cooke,
which one is it?

40:47.865 --> 40:50.909
Did you beat up Mr. Chapman
or did he beat you up like a rag doll?

40:50.909 --> 40:52.035
And when embarrassed,
you pulled out a knife?

40:52.035 --> 40:53.453
- Objection! Badgering the witness.

40:53.453 --> 40:54.454
- I just told you I ain't kill that man!

40:54.454 --> 40:56.039
Why the fuck you make it seem like that?

40:56.039 --> 40:57.165
- Sustained.

40:57.165 --> 41:02.296
♪

41:02.296 --> 41:03.422
- Nothing further, Your Honor.

41:03.422 --> 41:08.385
♪

41:09.761 --> 41:11.722
Finally, there's Rafael Coleman,

41:11.722 --> 41:14.183
who offers us
the most damning evidence of all.

41:14.183 --> 41:15.726
Mr. Coleman with his own eyes

41:15.726 --> 41:19.396
witnessed the defendant stab
Kevin Chapman in the midst of a brawl.

41:19.396 --> 41:22.065
He didn't say maybe it was Mr. Cooke.

41:22.065 --> 41:23.066
Or it might have been.

41:24.318 --> 41:26.153
No, he never wavered.

41:26.153 --> 41:30.699
And neither should any of you
in doing what is right and just

41:30.699 --> 41:33.869
by finding Damon Cooke guilty.

41:35.829 --> 41:36.830
Thank you.

41:38.582 --> 41:39.583
- Miss Nicholas.

41:41.084 --> 41:42.419
[clears throat]

41:42.419 --> 41:43.629
- Thank you, Your Honor.

42:00.771 --> 42:02.523
The people want you to believe that

42:02.523 --> 42:05.192
because Mr. Cooke
was at the bar that night,

42:05.192 --> 42:06.693
because he was in a fight,

42:07.569 --> 42:09.363
because he bought a knife,

42:10.113 --> 42:11.615
and because a witness

42:11.615 --> 42:15.202
who cut a deal
to save his own skin says he did it,

42:15.202 --> 42:16.828
that this is all enough to convict.

42:17.913 --> 42:19.331
Well, it's not enough.

42:20.707 --> 42:24.253
Damon Cooke has no violent past.

42:25.045 --> 42:28.382
He was simply in the wrong place
at the wrong time.

42:29.341 --> 42:33.804
Almost every generation
of Black families starts at zero.

42:35.097 --> 42:38.851
Damon Cooke, through his hard work
in his family business,

42:38.851 --> 42:39.935
broke that cycle.

42:41.520 --> 42:45.607
Today is your chance to break the cycle

42:45.607 --> 42:49.361
of convicting young Black men
of crimes they did not commit.

42:49.862 --> 42:53.156
Mr. Ortiz talked about
doing the right thing.

42:53.740 --> 42:58.328
The right thing is to acquit Damon Cooke
and send him home.

42:58.328 --> 43:01.123
♪

43:01.123 --> 43:02.249
Thank you.

43:02.249 --> 43:07.588
♪

43:22.811 --> 43:23.812
[cell phone buzzes]

43:33.155 --> 43:35.991
JUDGE COOMBS: The jury has
come to a decision in this case.

43:35.991 --> 43:37.826
The clerk will now read the verdict.

43:38.702 --> 43:41.121
- We, the jury,
find the defendant Damon Cooke

43:42.289 --> 43:44.458
guilty of second-degree murder.

43:45.417 --> 43:47.085
JUDGE COOMBS:
Mr. Cooke, you are hereby remanded

43:47.085 --> 43:49.630
into the custody of the sheriff
who shall transfer you--

43:49.630 --> 43:51.340
[audio fades]

43:52.216 --> 43:54.718
- Damon, I... I'm--
- I know.

43:54.718 --> 43:58.680
♪

43:58.680 --> 44:02.976
♪ Once I wanted to be the greatest ♪

44:03.602 --> 44:06.021
♪ Greatest, greatest, greatest ♪

44:06.021 --> 44:11.318
♪ No wind or waterfall could stop me ♪

44:11.318 --> 44:12.736
♪

44:12.736 --> 44:17.074
♪ And then came the rush of blood ♪

44:17.074 --> 44:21.578
♪ Stars at night turned deep to dust ♪

44:21.578 --> 44:24.122
♪ Melt me down ♪

44:24.122 --> 44:26.500
♪ Into big black armor ♪

44:26.500 --> 44:29.211
♪

44:29.211 --> 44:33.090
♪ Leave no trace of grace ♪

44:33.090 --> 44:34.758
♪ Just in your honor ♪

44:34.758 --> 44:36.927
♪

44:36.927 --> 44:39.346
♪ Lower me down ♪

44:39.346 --> 44:41.932
♪ To culprit south ♪

44:41.932 --> 44:44.768
♪ Make 'em wash a space in town ♪

44:44.768 --> 44:46.311
♪ For the lead ♪

44:46.854 --> 44:48.730
